snippet.textDisplay:
I agree that money and stuff won't make you happy, but it takes away one of the things you're trying to stir in your pie. I have gone from being a salaried commercial manager with awesome amount of spare money, to living on disability where my husband has to look after me rather than work, and we have 2 kids.
Trust me, not having money is extremely detrimental to my mental health. I'm so freaking anxious, I'm living on an overdrawn credit card and have had $0 for last 8 days. My pension isn't going far with everything being overpriced.
So yeah, money and stuff doesn't make you happy, you can have that and depression /anxiety. But fuck it's harder when you have depression and anxiety and no money with 2 little girls relying on you.

snippet.textDisplay:
Morgan Adams; THIS is your platform. THIS is the journey, story, situation, life, opinions, emotions and feelings that social media NEEDS and wants. Everything happens for a reason (believe that). Every moment, every thing you have been through has led you to where you are right now. Yes, heartbreak hurts, but it shows you what you want in a partner and friends.
Yes, anger hurts, but it teaches you patience.
Yes, sadness hurts, but it teaches you how to be grateful for what you have.
These journeys and feelings shape not only the world, but specifically your world. Don’t stop for people who don’t understand your vision. When they try to silence you, speak louder. Don’t give up. Don’t give in. You can reach people. Teach people. Show the real side of influencers, their lives, their strengths and weaknesses, good and bad. Be the truth of what others try to silence and hide. This video brought light to Me about how to heal and deal with my depression and pain I’m living.
Always Remember this:
“No One can make You feel inferior without YOUR Consent”. -Eleanor Roosevelt
Take back your power Morgan!
